我也遇到了类似的问题，生成交替颜色的行，结果所有单元格都是同一种颜色，我已经解决这个问题。
我是这样解决的，如果你设置了一个对象预设，例如：
```
row: {
    style: {
        fill: {
            type: 'pattern',
            pattern: 'solid',
            fgColor: { argb: 'FFFF0000' },
        }
    }
}
```

在给cell.style进行赋值时，应该是 

`cell.style = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(row.style)) `

而不是

`cell.style = row.style`

这只是设置了row.style的引用而不是拷贝，后面修改fgColor的值也只是修改原始对象的值，你需要拷贝row对象才行。

希望对你有帮助！

"I also encountered a similar problem, generating rows with alternating colors, but all cells ended up being the same color. I have solved this problem. Here’s how I solved it. If you have set a preset object, for example:

```
row: {
    style: {
        fill: {
            type: 'pattern',
            pattern: 'solid',
            fgColor: { argb: 'FFFF0000' },
        }
    }
}
```

When assigning a value to cell.style, it should be

`cell.style = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(row.style))`

instead of

`cell.style = row.style`

The latter only sets a reference to row.style rather than making a copy. Later modifications to fgColor only modify the value of the original object. You need to make a copy of the row object.

I hope this helps you!"
